    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large dry pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> cashews</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden, then transfer to a plate and reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-mushroom-edamame-and-mooli-noodles-with-cashews-and-an-egg/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>medium egg noodles</strong> to a pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>until fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy noodle water</strong>, and set aside</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-mushroom-edamame-and-mooli-noodles-with-cashews-and-an-egg/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-mushroom-edamame-and-mooli-noodles-with-cashews-and-an-egg/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until browned</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-mushroom-edamame-and-mooli-noodles-with-cashews-and-an-egg/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>ginger paste</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, your<strong> ketjap manis</strong>, <strong>mirin</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and most of your <strong>shichimi togarashi </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) in a bowl</p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>starchy noodle water </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-mushroom-edamame-and-mooli-noodles-with-cashews-and-an-egg/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms have browned, add your <strong>mooli slaw mix</strong> to the pan[s] and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat, once hot, crack your<strong> egg[s]</strong> into the pan then cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-mushroom-edamame-and-mooli-noodles-with-cashews-and-an-egg/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>drained noodles</strong> to the pan[s] with your <strong>teriyaki sauce </strong>and<strong> edamame beans</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce coats the noodles and everything is hot through \u2013 this is your <strong>teriyaki mushroom, edamame & mooli noodles</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy noodle water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/teriyaki-mushroom-edamame-and-mooli-noodles-with-cashews-and-an-egg/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>teriyaki mushroom, edamame & mooli noodles</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining shichimi togarashi</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>toasted cashews </strong>and the <strong>fried egg</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
